In the figure above right, explain why \triangle ABC is similar to \triangle FBE.  

Explain why \angle FDC = \alpha.

Write an expression in terms of \alpha and \beta for side CF.

Explain why \triangle FBE is similar to \triangle ADE.

Justify each equality in the statement
    \tan (\alpha - \beta) = \dfrac{DE}{BE} = \dfrac{AD}{BF} = \dfrac{\tan \alpha - \tan \beta}{1+\tan \alpha \tan \beta}

